article.headline: Northeastern 81, MD Baltimore Co 78
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Marcus Barnes scored 22 points and Jose Juan Barea had 14 assists to lead Northeastern past UMBC 81-78 Saturday afternoon. The victory was the Huskies' fifth win in six games and guaranteed Northeastern (16-9, 10-4 America East) will finish above .500 for the second straight season. The last time the Huskies posted back-to-back winning seasons was 1989-1990 and 1990-1991. UMBC (7-16, 4-10) trailed by as much as 54-37 early in the second half, but rallied to tie the game at 72 on a Kareen Washington 3-pointer with 2:09 left. Barnes responded with 3-pointers on the next two Huskies' possessions to give Northeastern a 78-72 lead, and followed with two free throws in the final 7.8 seconds. Many of Barea's assists came in spectacular fashion. During one sequence in the first half he switched hands midway through a jumpshot to find an open Bennet Davis under the basket. On the next trip down the floor, he beat four defenders that had converged on him with a behind-the-back bounce pass that Jesse Dunn converted into a 3-point play. Sylbrin Robinson scored 14 points for Northeastern and Javorie Wilson and Barea each added 13 points. Andrew Feeley tied a career high with 22 points to lead UMBC.
